body_html:
The point of my inquiry is because I want to use certain tf ops that pehaps only transpose the tensor shape and not necessarily operate on its data mathematically. DepthSpace and BatchSpace are two such ops that supposedly return the input tensor dtype.

Since quatization is not specifically supported for most/any commands currently it would help if those commands that don't operate mathematically on the data would just pass the input tensor type to the output unaltered. That is what the documentation says in the case of DepthSpace and BatchSpace.

Thanks in advance,
